parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the steering rack can cause the steering wheel to lock up or become difficult to turn, leading to loss of control and increased risk of accidents.
symptoms: The steering wheel feels stiff or hard to turn
the vehicle pulls to one side
clunking or grinding noises when turning

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the tie rod can cause the steering wheel to become loose or difficult to control, leading to loss of control and increased risk of accidents.
symptoms: Clunking or grinding noises when turning
the steering wheel feels loose or unstable
the vehicle pulls to one side
difficulty turning or controlling the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the power steering assist can cause the steering wheel to become difficult to turn or lock up, leading to loss of control and increased risk of accidents.
symptoms: The steering wheel feels stiff or hard to turn
difficulty turning or controlling the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Unintended acceleration can lead to loss of vehicle control, accidents, and injuries. The sudden and unexpected acceleration can cause the vehicle to surge forward, even when the driver is attempting to brake, which can result in collisions, property damage, and harm to occupants and pedestrians.
symptoms: The vehicle suddenly accelerates without warning
often when shifting into gear or when the driver is attempting to brake. The acceleration can be sudden and rapid
causing the vehicle to lurch forward or backward. In some cases
the vehicle may accelerate to high speeds
making it difficult for the driver to control.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure of the throttle body can cause the vehicle to stall, lose power, or accelerate unexpectedly, leading to loss of vehicle control, accidents, and injuries.
symptoms: The vehicle may experience sudden acceleration or deceleration
or stalling. The throttle body may need to be replaced
and the problem may recur even after repair.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure of the speed control/transaxle system can cause the vehicle to suddenly lose power or accelerate, leading to loss of vehicle control, accidents, and injuries.
symptoms: The vehicle may experience sudden loss of power
often when shifting gears or when the speed control module fails.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause various malfunctions, including failure of dashboard gauges, interior lights, and ignition systems, which can lead to accidents, strand the driver, or even cause electrical fires.
The wiring harness issues can cause electrical system failures, leading to malfunctions, electrical fires, and accidents.
The failure of the ignition system can cause the vehicle to stall or not start, leading to accidents or strand the driver.
symptoms: and difficulty turning the key in the ignition switch.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of interior lights can cause distractions, accidents, or visibility issues while driving.
